From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kairo RFC/POC <local@kairo.invalid>
Date: Sun, 21 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [RFC/POC] block: sketch Kairo scheduler dispatch stats

This local RFC/POC patch sketches the counters needed to validate the Kairo
scheduler hypothesis. The exact sysfs/debugfs integration should be adapted to
the target kernel tree.

This is not intended for LKML submission.
---
 block/mq-deadline.c | 41 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 41 insertions(+)

diff --git a/block/mq-deadline.c b/block/mq-deadline.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/block/mq-deadline.c
+++ b/block/mq-deadline.c
@@ -1,3 +1,44 @@
+/*
+ * Kairo RFC/POC scheduler stats.
+ *
+ * Intended counters for local validation:
+ *
+ *   kairo_decode_dispatches
+ *   kairo_prefetch_dispatches
+ *   kairo_prefill_dispatches
+ *   kairo_normal_dispatches
+ *   kairo_starvation_escapes
+ *
+ * These counters make the benchmark results explainable. If p99 decode-read
+ * latency improves, we need to show that decode-critical reads were actually
+ * dispatched through the Kairo lane and that writes were not completely
+ * starved.
+ */
+
+struct kairo_sched_stats {
+	u64 decode_dispatches;
+	u64 prefetch_dispatches;
+	u64 prefill_dispatches;
+	u64 normal_dispatches;
+	u64 starvation_escapes;
+};
+
+/*
+ * TODO integration options:
+ *
+ * 1. Add these counters to struct deadline_data.
+ * 2. Increment counters in dd_dispatch_request() or the local Kairo dispatch
+ *    path based on kairo_classify_request(rq).
+ * 3. Expose them through the scheduler sysfs attribute group under:
+ *
+ *      /sys/block/<dev>/queue/iosched/
+ *
+ *    Example files:
+ *      kairo_decode_dispatches
+ *      kairo_prefetch_dispatches
+ *      kairo_prefill_dispatches
+ *      kairo_normal_dispatches
+ *      kairo_starvation_escapes
+ *
+ * 4. Keep this local and experimental until the benchmark demonstrates value.
+ */
+
 /* existing mq-deadline code continues below in the target kernel tree */
